In loving memory of Victor Basil (Boyce) Pillay. This prominent Lowveld community figure lost his battle with Covid-19 on Monday February 1 and is now at rest. Victor was a well-known individual with many friends. He was influential in the motor industry and also served as a police reservist. He was a legend to his community, Valencia Park. He is survived by his son, Lance Pillay, and the larger Pillay family originally from Barberton. Rest in peace and rise in glory! ALSO READ: Community members mourn loss of Jackson Mthembu